    <abstract>
      <t>Congestion Exposure (ConEx) is a mechanism by which senders inform the network about the congestion encountered by packets earlier in the same flow.  This document specifies an IPv6 destination option that is capable of carrying ConEx markings in IPv6 datagrams.</t>
    </abstract>
  </front>
